metadata.name: pico_vibrations #44
metadata.description:
Something just for fun to explore some concepts like seed looping.

Source code:
```
pico-8 cartridge // http://www.pico-8.com
version 35
__lua__
_set_fps(60)

r=rnd
w=stat(6)
seed=1
for i=1,#w do
ch=ord(sub(w,i,i))seed+=seed*31+ch
end
if(#w==0)seed=r(-1)
srand(seed)

lines=r({-1,0,1})
fp=r({true,false})
--poke(24364,r({0,0,0,5,6,7}))
fillp(r({â–¥,â–ˆ,â–¤}))
for i=0,15do
pal(i,r(32)-16,1)
end
cls()

::_::

clip(16,16,96,96)

srand(seed)
x=r(64)+16
y=r(64)+16
for i=0,10do
line(x*r({1,-1}),y*r({1,-1}),y*r({1,-1}),x*r({1,-1}),r(6))
x+=r(4)-2
y+=r(4)-2
circ(x,y,r(30)+.5,pget(x,y)-1)
end

poke(0x5f54,0x60)
palt(0,false)
sspr(0,0,128,128,2,2,128-4,128-4)
for i=0,15 do
circ(rnd(128),rnd(128),rnd(64)+64,rnd(8))
sspr(0,rnd(128),128,rnd(5),rnd(128),0,rnd(5),128)
sspr(rnd(128),0,rnd(5),128,0,rnd(128),128,rnd(5))
end
poke(0x5f54,0x00)
palt(0,true)


--blur boxes
for i=0,40do
a=96
b=16
pset(r(a)+b,r(a)+b,pget(r(a)+b,r(a)+b))
end

if(fp)flip()
clip()
for i=0,lines do
x=r(96)+16
y=r(96)+16
line(x,0,x,128,r(15))
line(0,y,128,y,r(15))
end

if not rec then
if(btnp(ðŸ…¾ï¸))extcmd("screen")rec=true
if(btnp(âŽ))extcmd("video")rec=true
end
if(t()*100\1%500==0)rec=false

goto _
```

metadata.name: Alpinism #150
metadata.description:
â€œOnly those who will risk going too far can possibly find out how far one can go.â€ - T.S. Eliot

---

Alpinism is a tribute to the rugged and wild landscapes that rise around us. Which may at once intrigue, impress, intimidate, and inspire.

I am captivated by the mythology of these settings. Where natural shapes appear fantastical. A ridge line drawn by pen meets sky poured out from neon gradient. Where observation is made through the lens of imagination.

Each piece begins with the concept of a mountain landscape. A number of ranges are drawn by pen in one of three styles. Within each style is a spectrum of variation that produces different drawn qualities. The backdrop may be an imagined sky, an impossible sunset, a piece of parchment. A testament to the interpreterâ€™s memory of the scene. 

---
- Made with p5js in the White Mountains of NH July 2022
- press s to save png

metadata.name: Word-eating worms #226
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork.

An old letter recounts the problems and feelings caused by woodworms: worms known to eat not only the beams and wood of houses, but also old books. As an analogy to this daily occurrence, emoticons appear and with the good spirit of simplifying they begin to gnaw away so much literary flourish.

The piece puts in counterpoint two forms of communication: emoticons and traditional writing. Here an inevitable contrast is sought between the standardization of the feelings of emojis, and the excessive flourishes of texts, possibly already from other times.

Original flute (tap & frullato), cello (pizz) and marimba samplers.
((click to start sound))

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)

metadata.description:

The background consists of countless lines that create a halo-like state in the center. Various sizes and densities and more than 12 color palettes have been used.

metadata.name: Happenings #23
metadata.description:
Inspired by the chaos and imperfectly beautiful dynamics of parenting and life, 'Happenings' is the embodiment of the messiness, the unexpected and playful experiences that allow for the greatest depths of connection with our children.

Our intention was to evoke our deepest and most personal feelings as parents of young ones navigating the challenges of the pandemic while immersing ourselves in the Web3 arena.

This collection is Jimena + Marcosâ€™ first generative art collection in the Tezos blockchain via FX Hash, and consists of 222 1/1 artworks created with javascript.

metadata.name: EYES #62
metadata.description:
The beauty and soul of eyes have always fascinated me. There are billions of eyes in the world, all with different colors, textures and shapes and each one is still unique. With this project, I wanted to capture that natural beauty of the eyes, but also give them my unique colorful style.

Zombie and Cat eyes are more rare. Who will collect the Zombie Cat eye?

----

Created with the help of amazing cables.gl. For optimization purposes, in order to make the project load properly on fxhash, I had to use 2 textures for the eye pupil shapes instead of procedurally generating them. There is also hdr map loaded for the reflections.  

Press E to download the generated image.

----

All who collected NEBULAE were added to the reserve list. <3

metadata.description:

The Morixels Cats are unique Random Generated 500 PFP NFTs.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution.
The number of Traits in this collection is 8 (81 layers) and it has the ability to make 8,601,600 NFTs.
Some â€‹layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
